<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-05-23T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-05-21T00:29:00-05:00" n="556" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d556">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 837.00/1360</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Gonzales</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Habana</hi>
                                </placeName> [<date ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-content" calendar="gregorian" notAfter="1917-05-23T15:00:00-05:00" notBefore="1917-05-21T00:00:00-05:29"><hi rend="italic">undated</hi></date><hi rend="italic">; received May 23,
                                    1917, 3 a.m</hi>.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Reports from all over country show orderly celebration 20th May.
                            Apprehension in Habana kept people indoors till afternoon when immense
                            crowds joined in celebrating inauguration. No disorders or bad feelings.
                            Today liberals of consequence called at Palace and congratulated
                            President. No activity by insurgents or bandits anywhere today.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Gonzales</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>